<paragraph id="141936D21873FFE5FF35F89F4B8EF85A" blockId="4.[151,1436,1692,1933]" pageId="4" pageNumber="490">
Among the species of 
<taxonomicName id="D3A64D511873FFE5FE32F89F4A08F8C9" box="[448,563,1800,1823]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="26D2EAC01873FFE5FE32F89F4A08F8C9" box="[448,563,1800,1823]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="490">Signoretia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurring on the Indian subcontinent, this species can be easily recognised by its chocolate brown dorsum with median ochraceous stripe on the head and thorax and also by the angular projection on the clypellus in profile (
<figureCitation id="8C9D2A571873FFE5FDB2F8D84AAEF8BE" box="[576,661,1871,1896]" captionStart="FIGURES 66 – 79" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[159,1410,217,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 66 – 79. Profile of head and thorax of species of Signoretia. 66. S. aureola Distant; 67. S. dulitensis sp. nov.; 68. S. greeni Distant; 69. S. lunglei sp. nov.; 70 – 71. S. maculata Baker; 72. S. mishmiensis sp. nov.; 73. S. quoinensis sp. nov.; 74. S. rubra sp. nov.; 75 – 76. S. sahyadrica sp. nov.; 77. S. similaris sp. nov. 78. S. sinuata sp. nov.; 79. S. takiyae sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257129/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="490">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="D3A64D511873FFE5FD5AF8C74B07F8BE" box="[680,828,1872,1896]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sumatrana">
<emphasis id="26D2EAC01873FFE5FD5AF8C74B07F8BE" box="[680,828,1872,1896]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="490">S. sumatrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also a chocolate brown coloured species but differs from 
<taxonomicName id="D3A64D511873FFE5FF26F8E3490DF85A" box="[212,310,1908,1932]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="greeni">
<emphasis id="26D2EAC01873FFE5FF26F8E3490DF85A" box="[212,310,1908,1932]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="490">S. greeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in lacking the median pale stripe on head and pronotum.
</paragraph>
